org.pebble.core.encoding.ints.datastructures

Class IntReferenceListsStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pebble.core.encoding.ints.datastructures.IntReferenceListsStore

  • public class IntReferenceListsStore
extends Object
    Handles the storage of reference lists used in Pebble's compression algorithm. Provides useful methods to store and retrieve these lists.

    • Constructor Detail

      • IntReferenceListsStore

        public IntReferenceListsStore(int size,
                      int maxRecursiveReferences,
                      int minListSize,
                      IntReferenceListsIndex referenceListIndex)
        Initializes a IntReferenceListsStore capable to store at most size lists with no more than maxRecursiveReferences recursive references. If the number of lists exceeds size, it will overwrite the oldest list on the store.
        Parameters:
        size - maximum number of lists to be stored.
        maxRecursiveReferences - maximum number of allowed recursive references.
        minListSize - Minimum size of list required to be added to the store.
        referenceListIndex - index used to find the best reference list candidate.

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public boolean add(int offset,
          int recursiveReferences,
          it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.ints.IntList list)
        Adds to the store the list. In case the store is full it will overwrite the oldest list on the store.
        Parameters:
        offset - position of the list respect to the list of lists, starting from zero.
        recursiveReferences - number of recursive reference of the list.
        list - to append to the store.
        Returns:
        true when the list is added to the store and false when is not.

      • remove

        public void remove(IntReferenceListsStore.ReferenceList list)
        Removes from the store the given list.
        Parameters:
        list - List to be removed from the store.

      • get

        public IntReferenceListsStore.ReferenceList get(it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.ints.IntList list,
                                       int valueBitSize,
                                       int listIndex)
        Finds reference list to encode list.
        Parameters:
        list - List that will be encoded using the reference.
        valueBitSize - maximum number of bits required to represent the lists values in binary representation.
        listIndex - index of the given list.
        Returns:
        The best reference list in the store to encode list.. Can be null when there is not a good candidate available.
